TY  - JOUR
AU  - Charemza, Wojciech
AU  - Quandt, Richard E.
T1  - Models and Estimation of Disequilibrium for Centrally Planned Economies
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297144
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 49
IS  - 1
SP  - 109
EP  - 116
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The planned level of output is an important variable in modelling Centrally Planned Economies and the present paper discusses several disequilibrium models in which the plan level is an endogenous variable. A key relationship in such a model is the plan-adjustment equation which is the counterpart of the usual price-adjustment equation employed in models of free economies. Seemingly minor differences in assumptions lead to markedly different econometric models. The coherency properties of these are studied and several likelihood functions are derived. The most complex of the models includes both endogenous plan levels and endogenous prices.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297144
ER  - 



